<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1448] Add a node in ZK to tell all masters to shutdown.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1448</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, shutting down a multi-master HBase is a bit of a mess since the backup masters aren&apos;t pinged by the stop-hbase script. To shut them down, you have to do a hbase-daemons.sh stop master. Also, with master failover in place, the backup masters may try to come alive. This can be solved by adding a &quot;shutdown node&quot; in ZK on which all masters should be listening.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12426380">HBASE-1448</key>
